24.4 User Interaction
=====================

VM has been designed so that the VM commands can be executed in all
VM-related buffers: the Folder buffer, the Presentation buffer and the
Summary buffer.  This is achieved by storing in a buffer-local variable
`vm-mail-buffer', the identity of the Folder buffer corresponding to
any one of these buffers.  Whenever a VM command is invoked by the
user, VM calls a function called
`vm-select-folder-buffer-and-validate', which sets the current-buffer
to be the Folder buffer and performs various checks.  It also stores
the identity of the buffer in which the command was invoked in a global
variable `vm-user-interaction-buffer'.


